---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="DFOS Protocol"
  description="Ed25519 signed chains, content-addressed proofs, W3C DIDs. Verifiable identity and content without trusting the platform."
  landing={true}
>
  <!-- ═══ Hero ═══ -->
  <section class="hero hero--forest">
    <header class="site-header site-header--landing">
      <a href="/" class="logo">
        <img src="/dfos-logo-green.svg" alt="DFOS" />
      </a>
      <nav>
        <a href="/overview">Overview</a>
        <a href="/spec">Spec</a>
        <a href="/did-method">DID</a>
        <a href="/content-model">Content</a>
        <a href="/web-relay">Relay</a>
        <a href="/cli">CLI</a>
        <a href="/deploy">Deploy</a>
        <a href="/skill">Skill</a>
        <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos">GitHub</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <div class="hero-inner">
      <img src="/key-icon-green.svg" alt="" class="hero-key" />
      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        The proof is public<span class="period">.</span><br />
        The content is private<span class="period">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">
        Ed25519 signed DAGs &middot; content-addressed CIDs &middot; W3C DIDs &middot; MIT License
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a href="#get-started" class="hero-cta-link">Install the CLI</a>
        <a href="/spec" class="hero-cta-link hero-cta-link--dim">Read the spec</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Two Surfaces ═══ -->
  <section class="split-section">
    <div class="split-image">
      <img src="/painting-hand.jpg" alt="" />
    </div>
    <div class="split-text">
      <span class="section-label">T O P O L O G Y</span>
      <h2>Two surfaces<span class="period">.</span></h2>
      <p>
        The proof surface is public — signed chains of cryptographic commitments,
        verifiable by anyone with a public key and any standard Ed25519 library.
        The content surface is private — documents live in member-governed spaces,
        visible only to participants.
      </p>
      <p>
        The protocol defines the proof surface. It sees hashes, never documents.
        You can prove you authored something without revealing what it is.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ How It Works ═══ -->
  <section class="dark-section">
    <div class="dark-section-inner">
      <div class="concepts">
        <div class="concept">
          <span class="section-label">S T R U C T U R E</span>
          <h2>Signed DAGs<span class="period">.</span></h2>
          <p>
            Identity is a directed acyclic graph of Ed25519-signed operations —
            key rotations, content commitments, recoveries — rooted at a genesis.
            Forks are valid. Convergence is deterministic: highest timestamp, lexicographic
            CID tiebreaker. No consensus needed.
          </p>
          <p>
            The <a href="/did-method"><code>did:dfos</code></a> identifier derives from the
            genesis hash — self-certifying. Content chains use the same mechanics.
            The protocol doesn't know what a "post" is.
            <a href="/content-model">Application semantics</a> are a separate concern.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="concept">
          <span class="section-label">N E T W O R K</span>
          <h2>Verifying relays<span class="period">.</span></h2>
          <p>
            <a href="/web-relay">Web relays</a> are HTTP endpoints that independently verify
            every operation on ingestion. No trust between relays. Three peering behaviors
            compose the network: gossip, read-through, and sync. There are no relay roles
            or hierarchy — topology is emergent.
          </p>
          <p>
            Verification is a pure function. Given a chain and a public key, any Ed25519
            library returns valid or invalid. Offline, in any language. The
            <a href="/spec">reference implementation</a> is verified across
            TypeScript, Go, Python, Rust, and Swift.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="chain-diagram">
        <div class="chain-node genesis">genesis</div>
        <div class="chain-edge"></div>
        <div class="chain-node">rotate</div>
        <div class="chain-edge"></div>
        <div class="chain-node">commit</div>
        <div class="chain-edge"></div>
        <div class="chain-node">commit</div>
        <div class="chain-edge"></div>
        <div class="chain-node head">head</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Image Break ═══ -->
  <section class="image-break">
    <img src="/painting-deer.jpg" alt="" class="image-break-bg" />
    <div class="image-break-overlay">
      <img src="/key-icon-green.svg" alt="" class="image-break-key" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Get Started ═══ -->
  <section class="dark-section get-started" id="get-started">
    <div class="dark-section-inner">
      <span class="section-label">G E T &nbsp; S T A R T E D</span>
      <h2>Install the CLI<span class="period">.</span></h2>
      <p class="get-started-intro">
        One binary. Keys in your OS keychain. Local-first by default.
        <a href="/cli">Full documentation</a>.
      </p>

      <div class="install-primary">
        <div class="install-code install-code--wide">
          <code>curl -sSL https://protocol.dfos.com/install.sh | sh</code>
          <button class="install-copy" aria-label="Copy command">copy</button>
        </div>
        <p class="install-alt">
          Also available via
          <code>brew install metalabel/tap/dfos</code>
          and
          <code>docker pull ghcr.io/metalabel/dfos</code>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="quickstart-block">
        <div class="install-label">Quickstart</div>
        <pre class="quickstart-pre"><code set:html={`<span class="qs-comment"># create your identity</span>
dfos identity create --name myname

<span class="qs-comment"># publish your first post</span>
echo '{"body":"gm"}' | dfos content create -

<span class="qs-comment"># see it</span>
dfos content list

<span class="qs-comment"># run a relay</span>
dfos serve`} /></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Specifications + Resources ═══ -->
  <section class="landing-section">
    <span class="section-label">S P E C I F I C A T I O N S</span>
    <h2>Read the protocol<span class="period">.</span></h2>

    <div class="spec-links">
      <a href="/spec" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Protocol Specification</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">Chains, beacons, merkle trees, CID derivation, verification rules, test vectors</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/did-method" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">DID Method</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">W3C <code>did:dfos</code> — self-certifying, transport-agnostic identifiers</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/content-model" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Content Model</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">JSON Schema content types committed via content-addressed CIDs</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/web-relay" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Web Relay</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">Verifying HTTP relay with gossip, read-through, and sync peering</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/cli" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">CLI</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">Identities, content chains, credentials, relays — Linux, macOS, Windows</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/deploy" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Deploy</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">Run a relay with Docker, Caddy auto-TLS, peering, and container images</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/skill" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Claude Code Skill</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">AI-assisted CLI workflows — install the DFOS skill for Claude Code</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/overview" class="spec-link">
        <span class="spec-link-title">Overview</span>
        <span class="spec-link-desc">Why the protocol exists, design principles, chain topology</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <hr class="section-divider" />

    <ul class="resource-list">
      <li>
        <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
        <span class="desc">— design decisions, AT Protocol comparison, blockchain identity</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos">GitHub</a>
        <span class="desc">— metalabel/dfos — MIT License</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos/releases/latest">Releases</a>
        <span class="desc">— pre-built binaries for all platforms</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@metalabel/dfos-protocol">npm</a>
        <span class="desc">— <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@metalabel/dfos-protocol">dfos-protocol</a>, <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@metalabel/dfos-web-relay">dfos-web-relay</a></span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://schemas.dfos.com">schemas.dfos.com</a>
        <span class="desc">— JSON Schema definitions</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/llms-full.txt">llms-full.txt</a>
        <span class="desc">— full protocol content as plain text</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
    document.querySelectorAll('.install-copy').forEach(function (btn) {
      btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
        var code = btn.parentElement.querySelector('code').textContent;
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(code).then(function () {
          var prev = btn.textContent;
          btn.textContent = 'copied';
          setTimeout(function () { btn.textContent = prev; }, 1500);
        });
      });
    });
  </script>

  <!-- ═══ Closing ═══ -->
  <footer class="closing">
    <div class="closing-image">
      <img src="/painting-angel.jpg" alt="" />
    </div>
    <div class="closing-content">
      <img src="/key-icon-green.svg" alt="" class="closing-key" />
      <div class="closing-mark">DFOS Protocol</div>
      <nav class="closing-nav">
        <a href="/overview">Overview</a>
        <a href="/spec">Spec</a>
        <a href="/did-method">DID</a>
        <a href="/content-model">Content</a>
        <a href="/web-relay">Relay</a>
        <a href="/cli">CLI</a>
        <a href="/deploy">Deploy</a>
        <a href="/skill">Skill</a>
        <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://dfos.com">dfos.com</a>
      </nav>
      <p class="closing-credits">Yancey &middot; Ilya &middot; Brandon &middot; Lena</p>
      <p class="closing-credits"><a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos/blob/main/LICENSE">MIT License</a> &middot; 2026</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>
